Mineru's name, design and character are all inspired by concepts relating to Minerva, the Roman goddess of wisdom, strategy, production and music; each of these traits matching perfectly. Why is this relevant? Because one of her symbols is that of an owl, which Mineru's headpiece visually resembles. Rauru is also referred to as the King of Owls in TotK, wears a piece of owl jewelry and his OoT incarnation would shapeshift into Kaepora Gaebora, the owl from that game everybody hated growing up, to advise Link.

Furthermore, Minerva has served as patron and assisted numerous heroes, including Hercules. The boss you have to defeat to unlock Mineru sprouts additional limbs just like the Hydra with its heads, and in the end Link slays a serpentine dragon with numerous horns resembling the silhouette of the same creature. Even the half-breasted chiton and knee-length caligae you start the game with are pointedly Roman style.
